org.zamia.instgraph

Class IGTypeStatic

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.zamia.instgraph.IGItem
      • org.zamia.instgraph.IGContainerItem
        • org.zamia.instgraph.IGType
          • org.zamia.instgraph.IGTypeStatic
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, ZDBIIDSaver

    public class IGTypeStatic
extends IGType
    This is always intended to be a subtype of a regular IGType so not to duplicate all the information of the IGType this is built from. A static type can do everything the regular type can plus it can provide static information (i.e. IGStaticValue) about its range boundaries, enum literals and so on.
    Author:
    Guenter Bartsch
